class Solution {
public:
    int minimizedStringLength(string s) {
        unordered_set<char> unique_chars;
        for (char c : s) {
            unique_chars.insert(c);
        }
        return unique_chars.size();
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution works by counting the number of unique characters in the string, as any character that appears more than once can be reduced to a single occurrence by the given operations. This is achieved using an unordered_set to store unique characters. The size of the set is then returned as the result. 
